  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws and regulations targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement reporting requirements\n2. Conduct customer due diligence\n3. File suspicious activity reports\n4. Maintain records of financial transactions\n\nInternationally, organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) set global standards for combating money laundering. Penalties for violations can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
